A magpie impling jar is obtained as the result of successfully catching a Magpie impling, while also having an empty impling jar. A Hunter level of 65 is required to catch magpie implings.

This jar can be traded in singularly to Elnock Inquisitor for 3 empty impling jars, but this is not recommended due to its high value.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening a magpie impling jar gives 16,554 worth of loot, on average. This means opening magpie impling jars marks an average profit of −6,857 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −342,850 to get a hard clue scroll from magpie impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.

The following drop rates are provided by Jagex, unless otherwise specified.

Impling jar[edit | edit source]

An empty impling jar is returned when removing the loot, with a 10% chance of it breaking.[1]
